    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                <date>February 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1830</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I Recd your last letter I see the price to printing your<lb/> books
                is much more than you wrote to me before as I know<lb/> you will not publish it
                without some <sic>prosback</sic> of gaining something<lb/> by it I will say nothing
                now on the subject but leave it to<lb/> your <sic>judgement</sic> to do with it as
                you please, I would take<lb/> 20 or 30 copies of it as soon as they are printed but
                that<lb/> would be a poor chance for the rest, I wish you could do it<lb/> with some
                assurance of gain how ever if not at present, I am<lb/> sure in some short time you
                may be able to do it to advantage<lb/> I saw <persName>Mr Mordecai</persName> last
                week he said he would take a copy<lb/> but said nothing else he has not called here
                for 2 months<lb/> we are all well hope you are better of your could no news</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain your affectionate uncle <persName role="author">Zalma
                    Rehine</persName></p>
            <p>you Aunt and <persName>Mrs Depass</persName>
                <persName>Riana</persName>
                <persName>Abby</persName> and all your friends send<lb/> their love to you. Remember
                me kindly to <persName>Mr and Mrs Peixotto</persName><lb/> and the young
                    <sic>laydes</sic> and all my friends in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs Sel Marks</persName> desires to be remembered to
                you</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>to the Care of</p>
            <p>
                <persName>Mr A. C. Peixotto</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
